   if (dpL.empty()) {
       if ((int)dpR.size() > n+1) dpR.resize(n+1);
-      normalize(dpR);
       return dpR;
   }
   ```
   With this change, each DP vector is normalized exactly once at its creation or after a merge, preserving the intended invariant.

2. Risk Warning (Optional):  
   After removing these calls, ensure that no other path in `dfs` returns an un-normalized DP. In particular, do not re-introduce stray `normalize` calls elsewhere.  

